# Performance Profiling Standards

This document defines performance targets and profiling practices for mobile applications. All features must meet these budgets and be profiled before release.

---

## Startup Time Targets

### Cold Start (App Launch)

| Platform | Target | Acceptable | Poor |
|----------|--------|------------|------|
| iOS | < 2.0s | 2.0-3.0s | > 3.0s |
| Android | < 2.5s | 2.5-4.0s | > 4.0s |

Measured from process start to first interactive frame (TTI).

### Warm Start (Resume from Background)

| Platform | Target | Acceptable |
|----------|--------|------------|
| iOS | < 0.5s | 0.5-1.0s |
| Android | < 0.8s | 0.8-1.5s |

### Startup Optimization Checklist

- [ ] Defer non-critical initialization (analytics, crash reporting) until after first frame
- [ ] Lazy-load heavy modules (maps, camera, ML)
- [ ] Minimize work on main thread during launch
- [ ] Use pre-main metrics (Xcode Instruments, Android StrictMode) to find blockers
- [ ] Profile on low-end devices (not just simulators)

### Measurement

```bash
# iOS: Xcode Organizer or Instruments App Launch template
# Android: adb shell am start -W -n <package>/<activity>

# React Native
npx react-native run-ios --configuration Release
# Use Xcode Instruments for detailed trace
```

