## Frame Rate

### Targets

| Context | Target | Minimum |
|---------|--------|---------|
| Scrolling | 60 fps | 55 fps |
| Animations | 60 fps | 55 fps |
| ProMotion devices (120Hz) | 120 fps | 90 fps |
| Complex lists (100+ items) | 60 fps | 55 fps |

### Frame Budget

- [ ] 16.67ms per frame at 60fps (16ms at 60fps is acceptable)
- [ ] 8.33ms per frame at 120fps
- [ ] No frame drops during scroll (jank-free)
- [ ] Animations use native drivers (not JS thread) where possible

### Profiling Tools

| Platform | Tool | Use Case |
|----------|------|----------|
| iOS | Instruments (Time Profiler, Core Animation) | CPU, GPU, frame drops |
| iOS | Xcode Debug Navigator | Real-time FPS |
| Android | Android Studio Profiler | CPU, memory, frame timeline |
| Android | Perfetto | System-wide trace |
| React Native | Flipper, React DevTools | JS thread, bridge |
| Flutter | DevTools Performance | Frame rendering |

### Jank Prevention

- [ ] Avoid synchronous work on main/UI thread > 16ms
- [ ] Use virtualization for lists > 50 items
- [ ] Offload image decoding to background
- [ ] Prefer CSS/GPU animations over JS-driven
- [ ] Profile before and after changes that affect scroll

